The paper proposes a novel computational model for fibers and uses it to cluster fibers with a dictionary learning and sparse coding-based framework. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the study of microstructure measures, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The use of a metric that considers both geometry and microstructure measure suggests that the paper could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a preliminary analysis using HCP data, which could fall under the signal and image processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
